description:
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Job Title – MHICT Team Manager, Band 7&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Base – Pullman Place &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Salary – £38,890-£44,503&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Hours per week – 37.5 hours per week &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;We are looking to recruit an enthusiastic and motivated registered professional to join our management team for the MHICT (Mental Health Intermediate Care Team covering the West locality consisting of Gloucester and the Forest of Dean areas. The successful candidate will be joining the service during an exciting period of change with opportunities to be involved in service development work. The position will primarily be based at Pullman Place however managerial support at Colliers Court in Cinderford will be required.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;MHICT provides both Improving Access to Psychological Therapies (IAPT) service and Primary Care Mental Health (PMH) nursing service across the Gloucester and Forest of Dean areas. This role involves the operational management of Therapists and Nurses in the locality.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The role is in a busy and dynamic team, you will need excellent organisational skills, be responsive to change and have the ability to communicate effectively. We provide a supportive working environment and opportunity for ongoing development through training and appraisal. You will receive regular supervision to support you within your role. The successful candidate must be able to lead teams through change.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;We are keen to develop a more representative diversity of our senior staff and particularly encourage applications from those individuals with protected characteristics - in particular from BAME, LGBTQ and disabled candidates.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The qualification, training &amp; experience requirements for the role are underlined in the Job Description/Person Specification.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;For further information regarding this post, please contact Laura Williams, Deputy Service Director (Entry Level Services) on Laura.Williams@ghc.nhs.uk&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Closing date: 19th November 2020&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;Shortlisting date: 20&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;th&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt; November 2020&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The Trust aims to recruit and retain the best possible staff who, through the application of their skills, qualification and experience, will make a positive contribution to our business of providing quality health care services. It is the Trust’s view that the costs associated with moving house in order to take up a post with us should not restrict our ability to recruit the excellent people we need, therefore we support staff to relocate with our relocation policy. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;This post requires the post holder to be able to undertake all statutory and mandatory training and post holders must be able to undertake physical interventions. Fitness for physical intervention will be assessed by Occupational Health. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;A valid UK driving licence plus the use of own transport for business purposes is essential. For qualifying staff the Trust has a Lease Car Scheme in place and also offers a popular Salary Sacrifice Car Scheme with our partner Tusker.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;To ensure you fully understand how the Trust, as a Data Controller, will process and store your data please read the attached document ‘ Applicant and Staff Privacy Notice’ prior to applying for the role. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Candidates for any staff appointment shall, when making application, disclose in writing to the Trust whether they are related to any governor. Failure to disclose such a relationship may disqualify a candidate and, if appointed, may render him/her liable to dismissal. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
